    detail: "The Health section runs the same checks as `observer doctor` and renders one row per check: ✓ ok, ⚠ warn, ✗ fail. The indented bullet lines under a warn/fail are the remediation hints — the same text the CLI prints.\n\nThe checks: schema version · database integrity · DB size vs retention · adapter storage paths · antigravity family state · hook checksums (has a registered hook file been modified since observer wrote it?) · hook commands vs the running binary path (stale registrations after a binary move) · MCP registrations · pidbridge health · concurrent daemons (two observers on one DB) · codex hook trust · proxy routing gap (a routed tool kept capturing while ZERO proxy turns arrived — the daemon was down or unreachable while the tool ran; routed tools HANG in that state, so this row is the after-the-fact tell) · org enrolment + clock skew.\n\nChecks run when the section opens and on Re-run — deliberately not polled, because the DB integrity check costs real time on a multi-hundred-MB observer.db. All green earns the CLI's one celebratory line: all checks passed ★.",
